text: Vittoria Farnese (29 April 1618 – 10 August 1649) was an Italian noblewoman. She was born in Parma, the daughter of Ranuccio I Farnese, Duke of Parma and Margherita Aldobrandini, niece of Pope Clement VIII. On 12 February 1648 she married Francesco I d'Este, widower of her sister Maria Farnese. The couple had one child, Vittoria (1649–1656), and Vittoria died in Modena, giving birth to her. Francesco then married a third time, to Lucrezia Barberini, in Loreto in October 1654. ==Ancestry== ==References== Category:1618 births Category:1649 deaths Vittoria Vittoria Category:People from Parma Category:House of Este Vittoria Category:Italian people of German descent Category:Italian people of Austrian descent Category:Italian people of Portuguese descent Category:17th-century Italian nobility Category:Deaths in childbirth
